There is no cobblestone generator in this pack. You must gather pebbles and then convert other items into EMC to create more cobblestone.

Shift right click dirt to recieve pebbles.

Transmutation is staged so you must progress through the pack and level up your skills before you are able to create things such as diamonds from EMC. Be careful if you consume an item that you do not have the requirements for you will not be able to get it back out.

This quest will teach you some about the basics of Reskillable; the mod that is used for staging a large variety of things in this pack.

To get to the skill menu for Reskillable, press 'y' or click on the tab to the left of your inventory.

To start with I recommend using the level you got for completing the Tinker's Quest to level up technology. This will allow you to start using crafting tables so that you can further progress.

Open up the skills menu and select "Tech", and then hit the '+' sign at the top right to put your level into it.

Proceed to get some craft a Industrial Blast furnace. Once created you will need to build the multiblock structure using standard maching casing. It is a 3x3x4 structure with 2 spaces in the middle. You will need this in order to get steel which opens up other mods.

Later on you will need to put lava in those two empty spots as it will increase the max temperature.
Wrench is useful for picking up the tech reborn machines.
The glass fiber cables are better for power transfer.
Better machine casing means higher heat levels.

Each quest will give you some information about what gets produced from that tier's essence. Just keep in mind you will have to set up machines to automate and refine the essence into a usuable form of EMC. JEI will be able to help you get from the essence to the EMCable outcome, as well as, help you upgrade from one tier of seed to the next.

If you want to get into Astral Sorcery you will have to start by making an Orechid to get aquamarine ore.

Now that you have collected some aquamarine you can start getting into Astral Sorcery and create your first Luminous Crafting Table, and Resonating wand.

Start by placing down the crystal with direct line of sight of the sky and place a vanilla crafting table nearby. Next right click the crystal with the linking tool and then right click the crafting table. This will link the crystal to the table.

Note: The crystal you were given is not of the best quality, and you will be able to make better crystals as you progress through Astral Sorcery.
Use your linking tool to aim the crystal at a block of aquamarine. Overtime this will turn into rock crystal ore which you can break to get rock crystals.
To start making liquid starlight which has many uses your first task will be to create a lightwell. You can put aquamarine and rock crystals in it at night to convert into liquid starlight.
Create a Starlight Crafting Altar to learn more about Attunement.
Create a looking glass and start looking at the stars.
Upgrade your handheld looking glass to a full fledged telescope.
Using the linking tool link the crystal to iron ore and create star metal ore.
Craft some constelation papers and hold onto them to discover some information about the stars. You can sneak right click with your astral tome to store the written papers inside.
The next step in your journey is to attune yourself to a constelation that you have discovered. Create an attunement altar and when it lights up with the constelation you want jump in.
An altar to teach you the ways of the constellations.
Create a Starlight Infuser to start being able to infuse items with starlight.

Combine a rock crystal and star metal dust inside a pool of liquid starlight.

With a visible sky it will combine and grow into celestial crystals.
Create an Iridecent Altar to learn more about Radiance.
Create an observatory to be able to view faint constellations.

Create a Containment Chalice to allow for better storage of liquid starlight. When starlight infusion would normally drain starlight from the multiblock, it can instead draw the starlight from a nearby chalice. This saves you the need of having to replace the liquid starlight.
Create a Nether Cake and hand it in to get the obsidian required to make a nether portal.
Gather the resources for a Tinker's Construct Smeltery. This will allow you to use metal to make better tools and armor.

Tinker I/O allows for speeding up the melting process with a fuel input machine, and for faster solidifying using a smart output.

One of the best fuels in the game is added by Tinker I/O, and is called Solidified Fuel. It lasts 25 times longer than coal and is a lot cheaper EMC wise.
Create a creative energy cube, and never have to worry about power again.
Ever find yourself looking for more of a specific fluid? Well look now more for a limited time only get your infinite fluid needs here.
Complete your quest for being the best floral alchemist by creating a pool that gives infinite mana.
If you want more bang for your buck you can make Enhancement Crystals to upgrade your infinity gear even further.
Turn that infinite fluid into infinite gas.
When you decide you want to store all your items in a single ME cell, create a Creative ME Storage Cell.
Tired of taking a beating from mobs, and your troll friends? Create a set of Infinity Armor.
When you decide you want to be able to kill anything and anyone in one hit build a Sword of the Cosmos.
The first item you encounter that is more expensive than the maximum value of EMC you can hold.
Craft a Tome of Knowledge to learn how to create all items that have an EMC value.
Travel to the nether and kill blazes. Collect their rods and convert them to blaze powder. Throwing blaze powder into water will produce lava, so be careful.
Good Luck.
This will help you learn how to start making your own machines.
Kill mobs to get resources from their corpses.
Growing EMC
Creative items and items that are more expensive than the max long value in java. (This is a very big number)
